                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 767.70/103.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yesterday the Minister for Foreign Affairs, and later the Grand Vizier, told the
                    Ambassadors of the five Powers that the Sultan had decided to remain in
                    Constantinople but disclaims all responsibilty for the safety of its inhabitants
                    if the Bulgarians capture it. These communications were reported by the
                    Ambassadors to their Governments in identic terms, without recommendations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
